channel.title: Comments on: Korean band butchers “Smells Like Teen Spirit”

item.title: By: Logan Young
item.dc:creator: Logan Young
item.description: me so nauseous! herro, herro, herro...heer-rooo.

item.title: By: patrick
item.dc:creator: patrick
item.description: i made it to the pre-chorus, and it was wretched. i shudder to think what the chorus was like.
item.content:encoded: i made it to the pre-chorus, and it was wretched. i shudder to think what the chorus was like.

item.title: By: Eric Greenwood
item.dc:creator: Eric Greenwood
item.description: did you at least make it to the vocals? that's where it crashes and burns. the song probably should not be covered for at least 30 years. you automatically sound like a joke if you try it now.

item.title: By: patrick
item.dc:creator: patrick
item.description:
i didn't get through minute one. still, it's not the worst cover i've ever heard; i had the unfortunate pleasure of seeing several shitty high school bands attempt that song and fail miserably.
"smells like teen spirit" can't be that hard to cover, is it? or does every cover suffer from the song's ubiquitous and wholly unique place in the musical landscape? after all, wasn't this song the "anarchy in the uk" for the grunge generation?
item.content:encoded:
i didn’t get through minute one. still, it’s not the worst cover i’ve ever heard; i had the unfortunate pleasure of seeing several shitty high school bands attempt that song and fail miserably.

“smells like teen spirit” can’t be that hard to cover, is it? or does every cover suffer from the song’s ubiquitous and wholly unique place in the musical landscape? after all, wasn’t this song the “anarchy in the uk” for the grunge generation?
